<paragraph id="8BDB9B17317FBD003BE0FCE09E32A91C" blockId="6.[151,1436,845,1551]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">
One of us (RLW) examined the 
<typeStatus id="54DF25B5317FBD00397DFCE09D68AE54" box="[522,624,845,871]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">holotype</typeStatus>
(by monotypy), a male measuring 
<quantity id="4C9C36F2317FBD003F70FCE09B77AE54" box="[1031,1135,845,871]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.23" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="12.3">12.3 mm</quantity>
X 5.0 mm, labeled as follows: “Holo-type [red rimmed circle]/ 
<number id="3DAC8930317FBD00392EFCD89D9EAEBC" box="[601,646,885,911]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" value="402.0">402</number>
[h]/ Ventanas, Mex., 
<quantity id="4C9C36F2317FBD0038FEFCD89CC5AEBC" box="[905,989,885,911]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.096" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" unit="ft" value="2000.0">2000ft</quantity>
., Forrer/ 
<taxonomicName id="4C64E094317FBD003F36FCD89A5EAEBC" box="[1089,1350,885,911]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="socialis">Chrysobothris socialis</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="54DF25B5317FBD003E21FCD89A8AAEBC" box="[1366,1426,885,911]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Type</typeStatus>
) Waterh.” Ventanas is in Durango (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF5E6E6317FBD00395EFC309C4BAE84" author="Selander" box="[553,851,925,951]" pageId="6" pageNumber="58" refString="Selander, R. B. &amp; Vaurie, P. (1962) A gazetteer to accompany the Insecta volumes of the Biologa Centrali-Americana. American Museum Novitates, 2099, 1 - 70." type="journal article" year="1962">
Selander &amp; Vaurie, 
<number id="3DAC8930317FBD003863FC309C4BAE84" box="[788,851,925,951]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" value="1962.0">1962</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The frons is entirely coppery, the occiput green. There is a vague median longitudinal depression extending from behind the clypeus to about mid-point. The sides of the pronotum are narrowly, yet boldly, coppery-red except near the base. The ventral surface is coppery bronze.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37EC89C317FBD003BB1FB909B7BAB3C" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BDB9B17317FBD003BB1FB909B7BAB3C" blockId="6.[151,1436,845,1551]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">
<bibRefCitation id="EFF5E6E6317FBD003BB1FB909E72A964" author="Cazier" box="[198,362,1085,1111]" pageId="6" pageNumber="58" refString="Cazier, M. A. (1951) The Buprestidae of North Central Mexico (Coleoptera). American Museum Novitates, 1526, 1 - 56." type="journal article" year="1951">
Cazier (
<number id="3DAC8930317FBD003A53FB909E79A964" box="[292,353,1085,1111]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" value="1951.0">1951</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName id="4C64E094317FBD003A97FB909D45A965" box="[480,605,1085,1110]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="socialis">
<emphasis id="B9104705317FBD003A97FB909D45A965" box="[480,605,1085,1110]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">C. socialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Sinaloa, undoubtedly based on two specimens (
<collectionCode id="ED7503D2317FBD003FAFFB909A2DA964" LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" box="[1240,1333,1085,1111]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" name="American Museum of Natural History" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">AMNH</collectionCode>
) lacking additional data. He considered them female, but his description of the last visible abdominal sternite and our examination clearly show them to be male. We have compared them to the 
<typeStatus id="54DF25B5317FBD003F5EFB209B97A994" box="[1065,1167,1165,1191]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">holotype</typeStatus>
and consider all three specimens conspecific. We examined another specimen from Sinaloa, Estuilla Dist., Alamosa, 
<date id="FFDABDD7317FBD003F8CFB189A4AA9FC" box="[1275,1362,1205,1231]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" value="1933-10-02">
<number id="3DAC8930317FBD003F8CFB189A12A9FC" box="[1275,1290,1205,1231]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" value="2.0">2</number>
-X- 
<number id="3DAC8930317FBD003E43FB189A4AA9FC" box="[1332,1362,1205,1231]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" value="33.0">33</number>
</date>
, H. S. Gentry, 
<collectionCode id="ED7503D2317FBD003B80FB709E5FA9C4" box="[247,327,1245,1271]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">CASC</collectionCode>
. There is an “Alamos” in that state, near the coast, but we cannot find mention of “Estuilla” anywhere. The only published record (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF5E6E6317FBD00392DFAA89C24A82C" author="Nelson" box="[602,828,1285,1311]" pageId="6" pageNumber="58" refString="Nelson, G. H., Verity, D. S. &amp; Westcott, R. L. (1981) Additional notes on the biology and distribution of Buprestidae (Coleoptera) of North America. The Coleopterists Bulletin, 35 (2), 129 - 151." type="journal article" year="1981">
Nelson 
<emphasis id="B9104705317FBD0039C0FAA89DE9A82D" box="[695,753,1285,1310]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">et al.</emphasis>
, 
<number id="3DAC8930317FBD003877FAA89C24A82C" box="[768,828,1285,1311]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" value="1981.0">1981</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) of this species from Sonora must be referred to the following new subspecies (see below). However, we examined two specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C64E094317FBD003F38FA809BFCA875" box="[1103,1252,1325,1350]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="socialis" subSpecies="socialis">
<emphasis id="B9104705317FBD003F38FA809BFCA875" box="[1103,1252,1325,1350]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">C. s. socialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from that state: Río Mayo, Arroyo Guajaray, 
<number id="3DAC8930317FBD003A85FAF89D17A85C" box="[498,527,1365,1391]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" value="20.0">20</number>
&amp; 
<date id="FFDABDD7317FBD003942FAF89D83A85C" box="[565,667,1365,1391]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" value="1934-10-25">
<number id="3DAC8930317FBD003942FAF89D4BA85C" box="[565,595,1365,1391]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" value="25.0">25</number>
-X- 
<number id="3DAC8930317FBD00390BFAF89D83A85C" box="[636,667,1365,1391]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" value="34.0">34</number>
</date>
, H. S. Gentry, 
<collectionCode id="ED7503D2317FBD00383DFAF89C83A85C" box="[842,923,1365,1391]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">CASC</collectionCode>
. The only female of this subspecies that we have seen is labeled “Nayarit, 
<collectingCountry id="F373DB87317FBD00397AFAD09D72A8A4" box="[525,618,1405,1431]" name="Mexico" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, 
<date id="FFDABDD7317FBD00390EFAD09DC7A8A4" box="[633,735,1405,1431]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" value="1917-11">
XI- 
<number id="3DAC8930317FBD0039D3FAD09DC7A8A4" box="[676,735,1405,1431]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" value="1917.0">1917</number>
</date>
” (misidentified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C64E094317FBD0038B0FAD09BE1A8A4" authority="Waterhouse" authorityName="Waterhouse" box="[967,1273,1405,1431]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trisignata">
<emphasis id="B9104705317FBD0038B0FAD09B47A8A5" box="[967,1119,1405,1430]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">C. trisignata</emphasis>
Waterhouse
</taxonomicName>
), 
<collectionCode id="ED7503D2317FBD003E78FAD09A47A8A4" box="[1295,1375,1405,1431]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">CASC</collectionCode>
. The elytra bear distinct, extensive coppery reflections and reduced markings. However, in every other respect, notably the color of the underside, it matches the other specimens we examined. Including the 
<typeStatus id="54DF25B5317FBD003E75FA609A73A8D4" box="[1282,1387,1485,1511]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">holotype</typeStatus>
, the six males we saw range in length from 
<quantity id="4C9C36F2317FBD003916FA589C17AB3C" box="[609,783,1525,1551]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.215" metricValueMax="1.35" metricValueMin="1.08" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="12.15" valueMax="13.5" valueMin="10.8">10.8–13.5 mm</quantity>
, the female is 
<quantity id="4C9C36F2317FBD0038C0FA589B38AB3C" box="[951,1056,1525,1551]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.43" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="14.3">14.3 mm</quantity>
long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
